    "Overall, Happy-Tools showed similar or better performance in comparison to existing commercial software.",
    "In particular, HappyTools showed an enhanced throughput, demonstrating up to a ten-fold reduction of the total processing time for biopharmaceutical samples.",
    "The authors have released the source code and an executable program in an online repository to be employed freely for research purposes.In addition to HappyTools, there are other available opensource Python packages to analyze chromatographic and spectroscopic data.",
